text:
Ann Arbor is a city in and the county seat of Washtenaw County in
the U.S. state of Michigan. Founded in 1824 by John Allen and
Elisha Rumsey, it was named after the wives of the village's
founders, both named Ann, and the stands of bur oak trees they
found there. A college town, Ann Arbor is home to the University of
Michigan, which significantly shapes the city's economy, employing
about 30,000 workers. The city's economy is also centered on high
